            "part_label": "a",
            "question_text": "The function \\(h(x)\\) is defined as \\(h(x) = g(x) + 5\\). State the equations of the asymptotes of \\(h(x)\\).",
            "solution_text": "The graph of \\(h(x)\\) is the graph of \\(g(x)\\) translated vertically upwards by 5 units.\nThe asymptotes of \\(g(x)\\) are \\(x = 1\\) and \\(y = -2\\).\nTherefore, the asymptotes of \\(h(x)\\) are \\(x = 1\\) and \\(y = -2 + 5 = 3\\)."
